HEADWORD: Disenable
<hw>Dis`en*a"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>dis-</ets> + <ets>enable</ets>.]</ety> <def>To disable; to
disqualify.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sight of it might damp me and <qex>disenable</qex> me to
speak.</q> <rj><qau>State Trials (1640).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disenamor</ent>⟦br⟧
